<font color="#FF0000">REACTIONS TO THIS SITE</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec  4 15:04:39 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
When I was 14, in 1944, many, many members of my family were fighting against the Germans, and some in the German army.  I decided that I would try to stop World War III, through political action.<br>
So when Vietnam came, I was prepared.  I didn't protest, I ran a candidate for the US Senate in 1966. He got 50,000 votes in the Massachusetts primary.<br>
So this site allows me to revisit the time and the cause for which I took up politics as my calling.  I have nothing but praise for the soldiers who fought; I grew up with a father who had killed too many people too young [in the Russian Revolutions of 1905 and 1918]...  My task was to bring you men and women home as fast as I could.  I did my level best.<br><br>
I wish I could have done more.  I didn't stop until the last soldier came back.<br><br>
So I love this site, for the war was really what Maya Lin made it to be, a lot of human beings dying, and of course, many, many who came back to a mean and ungrateful America.  I who tried to get you back never blame you;  I blame the politicians who were ignorant and egotistical and mistaken.<br><br>
This site helps get these ideas out.  Maybe we can have a site for stopping future wars BEFORE they start.<br><br>
Thanks you all very much.
<p><code>-- center4c@tiac.net  (George Sommaripa) </code><p>


